===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|人|立|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=man|t2=stand}}. Often simply written as {{lang|zh|立}} in idiomatic expressions such as {{zh-m|即位}} in {{w|Western Zhou}} inscriptions.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*kV-r(j)əp||to stand}}. Derived from {{och-l|立}}. {{zh-ref|Mei (2012)}} lists it among the possible nasal-prefixed verb forms (Old Chinese ''*N-k-'' > Middle Chinese ''*ɦ-'', possibly forming a [[stative]]). Suffixed with a nominalizing ''*-s'', it takes the sense "the place/rank/status one holds".

